text.tspan: Alcohol and drug use disorders death rate, 2021

Estimated annual number of deaths from alcohol and
drug use disorders
per 100,000 people. These include
only direct deaths from these disorders, meaning they do not include suicide deaths which can in some cases
be connected or attributed to them.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2024)

Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is
age-standardized
.
